'''Jersey City Hoboken & Rutherford Electric Railway Co.''' was incorporated 1893, and leased from 1894-1899 to New Jersey Electric Railway Co.<ref>[http://www.scripophily.net/newjeelconew.html New Jersey Electric Railway Company - New Jersey 1894<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
The rail line in  was controversial at the time.<ref>[http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?_r=1&res=9A05E6DD1638E033A25750C0A9619C94679ED7CF&oref=slogin]</ref> Officials were concerned that an electric railway would endanger the public and frighten horses.<ref>[http://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9F02E3DA153EEF33A2575AC2A9679D94629ED7CF]</ref>